# Shrimp Fra Diavolo

> #fish #italian

![](D94118D1-799B-4A8B-9EC7-68ABF0018A74.jpg)

- Pasta | Linguine, 1/2 lb | 

Bring a large pot of salted water to boil and cook pasta to al dente while preparing the rest of the meal.

- Shrimp | Large, 1 lb, peeled deveined tail on | 
- Salt | 1 tsp | 
- Crushed Red Pepper | 1 tsp | 

Toss the shrimp in a bowl with salt and pepper flakes.

- Olive Oil | 3 tbsp | 

Heat the oil in a large skillet and saut√© the shrimp until just slightly under done. Set aside on a plate.

- Onion | 1, medium | Sliced
- Olive Oil | 1-2 tsp | 

Add onion to pan along with remaining olive oil and cook until translucent.

- Canned Tomatoes | Diced, 14 | 
- Wine | Dry white, 1 cup | 
- Garlic | 3 cloves | Chopped
- Dried Oregano | 1/4 tsp | 

Add tomatoes with their juices, wine, garlic, and oregano. Simmer until sauce thickens. About 10 minutes.

Return the shrimp along with any accumulated juices to the pan and cook for a minute so the flavors meld together.

- Fresh Parsley | Italian, 3 tbsp | Chopped
- Basil | 3 tbsp | Chopped

Stir in the parsley and basil. Season with more salt to taste and serve.
